            <span id="ChapterParagraphOne">
            <span id="BigFirstLetterText">M</span>y parents were people of few words. They didn't really talk too much, so we learned from how they reacted to adversity. For example, the time in their life they lost the house; the times in their life they had no jobs. They constantly had no jobs through all this time we were growing up in the family. I still remember that Dad said the moment I was born, he lost his job. <br />
            </span>

