            <span id="BigFirstLetterText">M</span>ore than their strength and courage, it is their intelligence and their perseverance that I admire. My parents only had one year of school in all their lives. It was called 㩧㩧齋 (pronounced “bok bok jai,” i.e. old-style private school). That was during World War II. My mom went to school for one year and learned how to read and write. So did my dad. Yet they had beautiful calligraphy. They could write better than I could in Chinese. They recited a lot of poetry that I could not recite, and I went to six years of Chinese school, and they only went to one year. They were very intelligent people.  <br />
