            <span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
            
               Evelyn and my dad were always having words. Evelyn was headstrong and Gong Gong was very headstrong. In Hong Kong, when Evelyn was nine years old, she went to get hot water and spilled it. She had hot water all over her body. When you get hot water on your body, you have to put some ice or honey on quickly or you scar for life. But Evelyn, being Evelyn, said, "I'm not taking my clothes off." Father said, "You take those clothes off!” "I'm not taking my clothes off." They were arguing back and forth, and eventually she took her clothes off so we could put some honey on her body. We don't know how Evelyn looks today, of course, and maybe it didn’t work, but I'm pretty sure it did. Honey has always been something that Gong Gong told us to believe in. He said, "This stuff is like the nectar of gods. You have to drink it every day." To the day he died, he always drank honey. Evelyn tells us that it was a miracle that he lasted so long. A lot of parts were not moving, not working, but somehow he still functioned.

 
