            <span id="ChapterParagraphOne">
            <span id="BigFirstLetterText">B</span>ack in Hong Kong, years ago, you didn't eat until Father sat down. That has always been a tradition in our family. When he sits down, you can start eating. All of the kids sit around, "Yap, yap, yap, yap, yap!", and don't touch the food. My mom taught us to always grab what's in front of you. You don't pick, pick, pick. Grab what is in front of you. You also eat every grain of rice on your plate, because that's to help you remember who brings in the money and who looks out for the family. By eating every grain, that reminds you the importance of being frugal.   <br />
